BaseBox<T> - Interface in com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.box
Box is a value holder, boxes are commonly used to modify variables from different scopes (or methods), example: int x = 0; Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> { x += 1; }; The value X needs to be "Local variable x defined in an enclosing scope must be final or effectively final"
A way to solve this is using Box, see example using MutableBox final MutableBox<String> x = MutableBox.of("Hey"); Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> { x.set("Hi"); }; For primitive types you can also use IntBox (or other variants).
BaseContainer<T> - Interface in com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.container
Container is a value holder, containers are commonly used to modify variables from different scopes (or methods), example: int x = 0; Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> { x += 1; }; The value X needs to be "Local variable x defined in an enclosing scope must be final or effectively final"
A way to solve this is using Container, see example using MutableContainer final MutableContainer<String> x = MutableContainer.of("Hey"); Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> { x.set("Hi"); }; For primitive types you can also use IntContainer (or other variants).
